WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.800
Hi, I'm Ichimaka Yannick from Ogale, and I'm Charlotte Galfand, and I'm super excited

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:17.920
to be introducing a workshop that we will be teaching at PositConf 2023, Steal Like

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:23.240
an Rtist Creative Coding in R. So there's many reasons why you should take our workshop,

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:29.360
but we're limited to three. I'll say the first reason is because it allows you to learn

00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:36.520
about creative coding. And so broadly, creative coding is when you use computer programming

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:42.599
for artistic expression. And both Charlotte and I are data analysts and visual artists,

00:00:42.599 --> 00:00:48.520
specifically genre of artists. And part of the reason why we are both is because we were

00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:56.240
able to leverage our background in R to create arts. There's a lot of overlap in the skills

00:00:56.240 --> 00:01:03.040
for both. And in this workshop, we will show you how you can like take your data transformation,

00:01:03.040 --> 00:01:08.800
your data manipulation skills, and your data visualization skills and create really great

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:13.959
art. We're taking an inspiration first approach to this workshop, starting by recreating existing

00:01:13.959 --> 00:01:18.480
works. If you feel nervous or intimidated, or like you don't quite put the creative in

00:01:18.480 --> 00:01:23.160
creative coding, this is a really good place to get started without already having an idea.

00:01:23.160 --> 00:01:27.680
Once you've recreated existing pieces, you'll have the activation energy to remix and reinterpret

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:33.199
them and eventually develop ideas and a style of your own. Finally, by joining this workshop,

00:01:33.199 --> 00:01:37.559
you'll become part of the artistry community at large, a group of people who make art using

00:01:37.559 --> 00:01:44.040
R. Artistry. Did you get it? Me and Ichimaka have very different styles and tastes, but

00:01:44.040 --> 00:01:48.440
we're constantly talking and collaborating when it comes to making art with R. Making

00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:52.519
art with a community or with friends is way more satisfying than doing it on your own,

00:01:52.519 --> 00:01:56.320
and way more encouraging to keep going. We're so excited for this workshop, and we can't

00:01:56.320 --> 00:01:58.320
wait to see you in Chicago. Bye!

